1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,280
Hello English learners, welcome back to EnglishPod.
英语学习者你们好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:06,280
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,280 --> 00:00:07,560
And I'm Erica.
我是Erica。

4
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:11,660
And today we're going to go back to the movies, but this time we're going to do it a little
今天我们要回到电影话题，但这次我们会有点

5
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:12,660
bit different.
不同。

6
00:00:12,660 --> 00:00:13,660
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:13,660 --> 00:00:19,040
We're going to be listening as two movie critics offer their opinion on the latest release.
我们将听到两位影评人对最新上映电影的看法。

8
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:24,320
Alright, so we're going to be learning how to criticize or give your opinions about something.
好的，所以我们要学习如何批评或表达对某事的意见。

9
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:25,480
That's right.
没错。

10
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:30,480
And here we're talking movies, but a lot of this language can be used to offer your criticism
这里我们谈论的是电影，但很多这种语言也可以用来表达你对文学、艺术或其他艺术追求的批评

11
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:36,320
or ideas on literature or art or other artistic pursuits.
或想法。

12
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:41,720
Okay, so before we listen to this dialogue for the first time, let's take a look at vocabulary
好的，在我们第一次听这段对话之前，先来看看词汇

13
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:44,080
preview.
预览。

14
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:45,080
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

15
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:49,680
Well, we're going to look at one word here that we will hear in the dialogue and it is
嗯，我们要看一个在对话中会听到的词，那就是

16
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:50,680
erudite.
erudite。

17
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:51,680
Erudite.
Erudite。

18
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,680
Erudite.
Erudite。

19
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:54,880
Okay, so this word erudite.
好的，所以这个词erudite。

20
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,720
Some people pronounce it erudite.
有些人发音为erudite。

21
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:57,720
That's true.
没错。

22
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:02,680
And basically it's an adjective describing someone who has a lot of knowledge about a
基本上它是一个形容词，描述某人对某个

23
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:03,680
subject.
主题有很多知识。

24
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:06,320
Okay, so an erudite in engineering.
好的，所以一个博学的工程专家。

25
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,440
Yes, or an erudite professor.
是的，或者一位博学的教授。

26
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,900
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

27
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,360
So that's the word that we're going to preview today.
这就是我们今天要预览的词。

28
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:25,520
And now let's listen to our dialogue and find out what movie they are criticizing.
现在让我们听一下对话，看看他们在批评哪部电影。

29
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:29,120
Welcome back movie lovers to another premiere movie review.
欢迎回来，电影爱好者们，来到另一场首映电影评论。

30
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:34,360
My name is Richard Clark and I am joined today by the very erudite David Watson.
我是Richard Clark，今天和我一起的是非常博学的David Watson。

31
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,620
Thank you, Dick.
谢谢你，Dick。

32
00:01:35,620 --> 00:01:38,240
Today we're going to talk about the movie Lion King.
今天我们要谈论电影《狮子王》。

33
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,320
Tell me, what is your impression of this film?
告诉我，你对这部电影的印象是什么？

34
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:45,560
Well, I think this film is simply a fable depicting man's eternal greed for power.
嗯，我认为这部电影只是一个寓言，描绘了人类对权力永恒的贪婪。

35
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:48,180
And in my opinion, it's a very fine film.
在我看来，这是一部非常好的电影。

36
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:52,920
Even despite the accusations of plagiarism of traditional folk tales from other countries,
尽管有抄袭其他国家传统民间故事的指控，

37
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,540
the musical score was amazing.
但配乐非常出色。

38
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:58,120
The animation was very well done and the story was simply enchanting.
动画做得很好，故事也很迷人。

39
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,480
I think otherwise.
我持不同意见。

40
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:03,040
Even though the animation was technically strong and as you say, the score and songs
尽管动画技术上很扎实，而且如你所说，配乐和歌曲

41
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,840
performed by Elton John were great.
埃尔顿·约翰的表演非常棒。

42
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:07,040
The film lacks certain originality.
这部电影缺乏一定的原创性。

43
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,260
It lacked heart.
它缺少情感内核。

44
00:02:08,260 --> 00:02:10,760
And I would dare to say it was too predictable.
我敢说它太 predictable 了。

45
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:11,760
Predictable?
predictable？

46
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,760
How?
怎么 predictable 了？

47
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:14,120
Come on, Dave.
得了吧，Dave。

48
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,120
It's a G-rated movie.
这是部 G 级电影。

49
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,000
It's for the kids.
是给孩子们看的。

50
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,000
It's not a thriller.
又不是惊悚片。

51
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,740
Well, that's just it.
嗯，问题就在这儿。

52
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,800
It did have some very dramatic and intense scenes.
它确实有一些非常戏剧化和紧张的场景。

53
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:26,720
For example, when Mufasa dies or the dark, grim portrayal of Scar.
比如木法沙去世，或者刀疤那阴暗、冷酷的刻画。

54
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,880
Even so, the film is linear.
即便如此，这部电影的剧情是线性的。

55
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,120
Mufasa dies.
木法沙死了。

56
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,080
Simba runs away thinking it's his fault.
辛巴跑开，以为是自己害的。

57
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,400
Falls in love and returns to retake what's rightfully his.
坠入爱河，然后回来夺回本该属于他的东西。

58
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,280
It's just too cliche.
这太老套了。

59
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,560
How can it be cliche?
怎么会老套呢？

60
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,120
It's a fable.
这是个寓言故事。

61
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,040
It's telling a time-honored story.
它在讲述一个经久不衰的故事。

62
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:45,320
The movie makes a point of how the hunger of power leads to corruption and teaches children
这部电影强调了权力欲望如何导致腐败，并教导孩子们

63
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:48,700
of the value of respect, life, and love.
尊重、生命和爱的价值。

64
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:53,320
You have always been so soft, Dick.
你一直这么心软，Dick。

65
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,960
Open your heart, Dave.
敞开心扉吧，Dave。

66
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:55,960
Don't shut us out.
别把我们拒之门外。

67
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,880
Anyway, that's all for today, folks.
好了，各位，今天就到这里。

68
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:00,760
Join us next time as we talk about How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days.
下次我们聊聊《十天丢个郎》，记得加入我们。

69
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:09,560
I'm sure you'll love that one, Dick.
我相信你一定会喜欢那部的，Dick。

70
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,560
All right.
好吧。

71
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,200
So The Lion King, one of my all-time favorites.
所以《狮子王》，我最爱的电影之一。

72
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:15,080
A very good movie and, well, mixed feelings about it, right?
一部非常好的电影，嗯，对它感觉复杂，对吧？

73
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:17,360
Some people think it's good.
有些人觉得它好。

74
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,640
Other people think it's not that good.
有些人觉得它没那么好。

75
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,280
I'm in the good camp, as you know.
我站在觉得它好的一边，你知道的。

76
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:26,800
But anyway, there's tons of really useful and quite difficult language here.
但不管怎样，这里有很多非常有用且相当难的语言点。

77
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:32,040
So why don't we look at that now in Language Takeaway.
所以我们不如在“语言摘录”环节来看看。

78
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,040
Language Takeaway.
语言摘录。

79
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,040
All right.
好的。

80
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:40,000
On Language Takeaway today, we have five words and we can start with the first one.
今天的“语言摘录”环节，我们有五个词，先从第一个开始。

81
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:45,800
So the first critic said that this was a movie depicting man's eternal greed for power.
所以第一位评论家说，这是一部描绘人类对权力永恒贪婪的电影。

82
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,800
Depicting.
描绘。

83
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,800
To depict.
描绘。

84
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,800
All right.
好的。

85
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,120
So this word, depict, it sounds a little bit strange.
所以这个词，depict，听起来有点奇怪。

86
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:57,680
So before we explain it, let's take a look at some examples.
所以在解释它之前，我们先看一些例子。

87
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,200
Example one.
例子一。

88
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:04,440
I don't really like the way that novel depicted the role of women in society.
我不太喜欢那部小说描绘女性在社会中角色的方式。

89
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:08,440
It was pretty sexist.
它相当性别歧视。

90
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:11,080
Example two.
例子二。

91
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:17,300
A film depicts the realities of war very accurately.
一部电影非常准确地描绘了战争的现实。

92
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:20,160
Example three.
例子三。

93
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:23,880
Apparently this image here is depicting some of the most well-known scenes from Australian
显然，这张图片描绘了澳大利亚一些最著名的场景，

94
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:24,880
history.
历史。

95
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:25,880
All right.
好的。

96
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:26,880
So depicting.
所以是描绘。

97
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:32,480
I can basically understand that this means to show something.
我基本上能理解，这意味着展示某物。

98
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:39,320
Now we can notice that the word depict has this short little word picked in there that
现在我们可以注意到，单词 depict 里面包含了一个短小的词，听起来像 picture。

99
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,000
sounds like picture.
当我们想到描绘时，通常是在图片、书籍或绘画中。

100
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:46,680
And when we think about depicting, we're often thinking about in a picture or in a book or
所以在这种情况下，故事是在电影中被描绘的，对吧？

101
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:47,680
in a painting.
没错。

102
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:51,240
So in this case, the story is depicted in a movie, right?
所以你可以看到它。

103
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,240
That's right.
基本上就是一幅画面。

104
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,240
So you can see it.
完全正确。

105
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,240
It's a picture, basically.
好的。

106
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,240
Exactly.
很好。

107
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,240
All right.
所以是描绘。

108
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,240
Very good.
好的，继续，评论家还谈到了对电影反派角色刀疤的阴郁刻画。

109
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,240
So to depict.
刀疤。

110
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:02,120
Well, moving on, the critic also talked about the grim portrayal of the villain of the movie,
没错。

111
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,120
Scar.
所以是阴郁的刻画。

112
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,120
That's right.
一个阴郁的刻画。

113
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,680
So grim portrayal.
好的。

114
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,160
A grim portrayal.
我们先看看 grim 这个词。

115
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,200
Okay.
当某物是 grim 时，它非常令人不快、不舒服，甚至想到它都让人震惊。

116
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,600
Let's look at the word grim first.
好的。

117
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:15,560
When something is grim, it's really unpleasant or uncomfortable or even shocking to think
所以我们会用一些阴郁的东西。

118
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,560
about.
好的。

119
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,560
Okay.
所以我们会用一些阴郁的东西。

120
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,560
So we're going to use something that is grim.
好的。

121
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,260
Now what about portrayal?
那“portrayal”是什么意思呢？

122
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:21,760
Really close to depict.
非常接近“描绘”的意思。

123
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:27,880
A portrayal is something that shows or describes something, especially like in a book or in
“Portrayal”是指展示或描述某事物的东西，尤其是在书中、

124
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,360
a picture or in a play.
图片或戏剧里。

125
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,360
Okay.
好的。

126
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,360
So a portrayal.
所以是“portrayal”。

127
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:34,000
I guess we can relate it again to a portrait.
我想我们可以把它和“portrait”（肖像）联系起来。

128
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,000
That's right.
没错。

129
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,000
All right.
好的。

130
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
So portrayal.
所以是“portrayal”。

131
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,480
Now we can also use this as a verb, to portray.
我们也可以把它用作动词，“to portray”。

132
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:42,880
So this movie portrays man's eternal greed.
所以这部电影描绘了人类永恒的贪婪。

133
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:43,880
Okay.
好的。

134
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:47,160
So we can use this as a noun or as a verb.
所以我们可以把它用作名词或动词。

135
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,160
That's right.
没错。

136
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:52,200
So moving on with our third word today, we have an enchanting movie.
那么继续我们今天的第三个词，我们有一个“enchanting movie”。

137
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,200
That's right.
没错。

138
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,400
The story was simply enchanting.
这个故事简直令人着迷。

139
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,400
Okay.
好的。

140
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,960
So if something is enchanting.
所以如果某事物是“enchanting”。

141
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:04,160
It's really attractive and beautiful and interesting and it holds your attention.
它非常吸引人、美丽、有趣，并且能抓住你的注意力。

142
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,160
Okay.
好的。

143
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,160
It holds your attention.
它抓住你的注意力。

144
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,920
So it's something very nice.
所以是非常好的东西。

145
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,760
Something that is enchanting has to be nice.
“Enchanting”的东西必须是好的。

146
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:10,760
That's right.
没错。

147
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:12,760
And it has this sense of magic around it.
而且它带有一种魔幻的感觉。

148
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,760
Okay.
好的。

149
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,760
Very good.
非常好。

150
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,120
So an enchanting moment.
所以是“an enchanting moment”。

151
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,840
Or an enchanting woman.
或者“an enchanting woman”。

152
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:18,840
Okay.
好的。

153
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,680
And now what about our next word?
那我们的下一个词呢？

154
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,080
It's a very...
这是一个非常...

155
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,160
And what about our next word?
那我们的下一个词呢？

156
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:26,240
It's French actually, but we use it in English.
它其实是法语词，但我们在英语中使用。

157
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,240
That's right.
没错。

158
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,960
So the critics said that this story was cliché.
所以评论家说这个故事很“cliché”。

159
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:30,960
Cliché.
“Cliché”。

160
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:31,960
Cliché.
“Cliché”。

161
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:32,960
Okay.
好的。

162
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,840
So we hear this all the time.
所以我们经常听到这个。

163
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:35,840
What is a cliché?
什么是陈词滥调？

164
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:43,180
Well, basically, a cliché is a phrase or an idea that is used so often that it loses
嗯，基本上，陈词滥调是一个短语或想法，因为使用得太频繁而失去

165
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:46,200
its meaning or importance or interest.
它的意义、重要性或趣味性。

166
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,200
Okay.
好的。

167
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:52,640
So can you give us some examples of a cliché moment or maybe a phrase that's cliché?
那你能给我们举一些陈词滥调的例子吗，比如某个场景或短语？

168
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,640
Okay.
好的。

169
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:54,640
Well, how about this one?
嗯，这个怎么样？

170
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:58,520
When you're breaking up with your boyfriend and you say, honey, it's not you.
当你和男朋友分手时说，亲爱的，不是你的问题。

171
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,520
It's me.
是我的问题。

172
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,520
Okay.
好的。

173
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,520
That's cliché.
这就是陈词滥调。

174
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,520
